<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-201-166 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 611 131</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  March 13 1991 n154 p19(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business andamp; Computer Publications(England) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>BSA settles Marconi theft action out of court. (British SoftwareAlliance suit against Marconi Electronics)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Marconi Electronic Devices Ltd. (Cases).andO;Topic:     Software PiracyLegal IssuesCourt CasesBritish Software AllianceLaw Suit.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>BSA settles Marconi theft action out of court Only weeks after the BritishSoftware Alliance filed an historic civil suit against Marconi Electronicsfor alleged software theft, the two parties have agreed to settle theirdifferences out of court.andM;Fox Borgerhoff Mulder, legal counsel for Lotus and the BSA, refused to giveany details about the settlement, commenting that the terms of the agreementare -- and will remain -- completely confidential.andM;The case, which was announced shortly before Christmas, was presented by theBSA as a breakthrough for software protection.andP;  Despite the subdued outcome,however, Borgerhoff Mulder denied that the result was a failure for the BSA.andM;He also refuted suggestions that the outcome of this case would deter the BSAfrom prosecuting other companies in similar circumstances.andM;Peter Smith, Marconi Instruments' UK managing director, still maintains thathis company was innocent of any kind of infringement or software theft.andP;  Hecommented: &quot;The basis on which the BSA acted was not true.&quot;andM;Smith feels that it would have been &quot;more gentlemanly&quot; to deal with thematter outside court.andP;  Despite this, he is eager to demonstrate his supportfor the BSA and the principles they defend.andM;Lotus UK managing director Paul Bailey gave no indication that this casewould cause any changes to his company's plans for litigaton.andP;  &quot;We will notstop taking people to court until the ratio of software sales to PCs actuallygoes above one copy per PC,&quot; he said.andO;</TEXT></DOC>